{{Infobox book | name = Trend Following: Learn to Make Millions in Up or Down Markets | orig title = | translator = | image = Trend Following.jpg | caption = | author = [[Michael Covel]] | cover_artist = | country = | language = | series = | subject = | genre = [[Business]], [[Non-fiction]] | publisher = [[FT Press|Financial Times Press]] (USA) | release_date = 2009 (USA) | media_type = Print | pages = 464 | isbn = 013702018X | preceded_by = | followed_by = The Complete TurtleTrader: The Legend, the Lessons, the Results }}
'''''Trend Following: Learn to Make Millions in Up or Down Markets''''' is an international [[bestseller]] written by [[Michael Covel]].<ref name=hedgefonder>[http://hedgefonder.nu/2011/09/michael-covel-trend-followings-ambassador/ Michael Covel: Trend Following Ambassador] ''Hedge Fonder''. January 9, 2011.</ref> It is about the investment strategy known as [[trend following]], which utilizes the [[Market trends|market trend]] mechanism and benefits from both sides of the [[Financial instruments|market]], enjoying profits from ups and downs of the stock or futures markets.<ref>Skypala, Pauline. [http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/fe36868a-ae32-11e1-94a7-00144feabdc0.html#axzz1zQjUBxPn Secrets of winning systems remain hidden]. ''Financial Times''. June 9, 2012.</ref>
==Release and reception== The book was an international bestseller, with the publisher reporting over 100,000 copies sold to date.<ref name=covelpublisher>[http://www.michaelcovel.com/all-versions-of-michael-covel-books/ Michael Covel Books] ''Michael Covel''.</ref> It was named top book about trading and commodity markets for last 15 years.<ref name=refco>[http://www.trendfollowing.com/whitepaper/broker-ref.pdf Trading Books] ''REFCO''.</ref>
